    <string name="privacy_policy_content" translatable="false">
<![CDATA[
<b>Privacy Policy for NoTrace</b><br><br>
Last updated: February 27, 2026<br><br>
<b>1. Data Collection</b><br>
NoTrace is a privacy-first application. We do NOT collect, store, or transmit any personal information, location data, or scanning results to any external servers. All data processed by the app remains strictly on your local device.<br><br>
<b>2. Permissions</b><br>
- <b>Bluetooth/Nearby Devices:</b> Used solely to scan for potential spy devices.<br>
- <b>Location:</b> On some Android versions, location permission is required by the system to perform Bluetooth scans. We do not use or store your physical location.<br><br>
<b>3. Data Storage</b><br>
Detection history and settings are stored in an encrypted format on your device. You can clear this data at any time from the app settings.<br><br>
<b>4. Third-Party Services</b><br>
NoTrace does not use any third-party analytics, advertisements, or tracking SDKs.
]]>
